decision_conditions:
This decision confirms the Council's agreement that the following alternative wording of condition 2 of permission P2019/0549/S73 is acceptable:

"CONDITION (APPROVED DOCUMENTS AND DRAWINGS): The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with the following approved drawings and information:

Drawing Numbers FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0010 Rev P01; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0099 Rev P04; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0120 Rev P01; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0101 Rev P06; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0102 Rev P03; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0103 Rev P03; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0104 Rev P06; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0105 Rev P06; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0106 Rev P06; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0107 Rev P03; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0108 Rev P02; FAW-JRA-00-04-DR-A-0109 Rev P03; FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0153 Rev P09; FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0154 Rev P08; FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0155 Rev P02; FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0156 Rev P02;  FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0157 Rev P04;  FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0158 Rev P02;  FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0180 Rev P06;  FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0190 Rev P01; FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0500 Rev P01; FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0505 Rev P01; FAW-JRA-00-ZZ-DR-A-0510 Rev P01; FAW-JRA-ZZ-ZZ-DR-A-0171 Rev P01;  FAW-JRA-ZZ-ZZ-DR-A-0172 Rev P01;
Planning Statement (incl. Statement of Community Involvement) by Gerald Eve LLP; Cover Letter (s73) by Gerald Eve dated January 2019; 
D&A Statement by John Robertson Architects dated June 2013; D&A Statement Addendum dated January 2019 Rev 3;
Environmental Statement Volume I
Environmental Statement Volume II
Environmental Statement Volume III
Environmental Statement Non-Technical Summary
Addendum to Environmental Statement and Revised Energy Strategy, dated June 2013
Second Environmental Statement Addendum by AECOM dated February 2019; Addendum to the Energy Strategy dated January 2019;
URS Cardinal Place - Future Climate Scenario Modelling - Document Reference 46369011-01 dated November 2012;
URS Energy Strategy Addendum Note - Document Reference 46369011 dated 16th August 2012;
Daylight, Sunlight and Overshadowing Assessment by Point Surveyors dated January 2019;
Addendum to the Environmental Statement Sustainability Chapter and BREEAM Pre-Assessment dated January 2019; 
Farringdon West - Transport Assessment Addendum dated February 2019; 
Gerald Eve Security Report Reference1934/Reports/190823/Ref/ER dated August 2019;
Security Needs Assessment by Sweco Reference SWECO-002-2019 dated August 2019; 

REASON: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interests of proper planning."

It also confirms the Council's agreement that following alternative wording of condition 11 is acceptable:

"The ground floor commercial units hereby approved shall be laid out as shown on drawing FAW-JRA-ZZ-GF-DR-A-0120 and shall not be amalgamated unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority.

REASON: The consideration of the acceptability of the commercial units was based on the proposed size of units as shown on the approved plans; the amalgamation or further subdivision of the units is likely to have operational, transportation, security and amenity implications, which should be the subject of consultation and a full planning application. The prevention of amalgamation / division of units would ensure compliance with policies: 6.7; 7.2; 7.4 and 7.6 of the London Plan 2016, policy CS14D of the Islington Core Strategy 2011 and Development Management Policy DM4.8."
